title: Paris Review editor says new Houellebecq book misunderstood
text: > Entertainment Paris Review editor says new Houellebecq book misunderstood FOR STORY SLUGGED EU BOOKS HOULLEBECQ SUBMISSION BY GREG KELLER - FILE - In This Nov. 8 2010 file photo, novelist Michel Houellebecq answers reporters after he won the France's top literary prize, the Goncourt, with his book "La carte et le territoire," or "The map and the territory ", in Paris. The latest novel by Houellebecq, the bad boy of French letters, has been called everything from an Islamophobic rant to a “French literary suicide.” Imagining the election of a Muslim president in France, “Submission” struck a raw nerve when it came out this year on the same day as the Charlie Hebdo attacks in Paris. (AP Photo/Thibault Camus, File)
